Wow! Outstanding! Based on past reviews, I reduced the stock, coconut milk, and fish sauce. It was wonderful, but I'm not sure the reduction was necessary. This dish is meant to be served in a soup bowl and the excess broth will be absorbed by the jasmine rice. So, next time, I'll follow the recipe as written. I do think substituting brown sugar for the white is reasonable, since it's similar to the traditional palm sugar often used in Thai cooking. We loved this recipe, and I'm looking forward to trying it with chicken. I did make a shrimp stock from the shells, and next time I will likely substitute it for the chicken stock.

