Rating: 4
My family loves this, it's so simple and flexible, but sooo good! Every time I make it I think it gets better and better. I use 1/3 cup chicken broth and brown sugar instead of white. Some simple variations on this basic recipe: add two med zuchinni (and/or tender yellow squash), halved lenghthwise and sliced; one or two big handfulls of frozen peas; the same of fresh or frozen diced carrots- let the veggies soften up in the curry before adding shrimp. Also for a nice change, add a small can of pineapple chunks with the juice & skip the chicken broth. Serve with lots of sticky rice to soak up that curry! Yum!

